Package org.modelio.archimate.metamodel.core.generic

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ActiveStructureElement
    ActiveStructureElement vnull These can be subdivided into : internal active structure elements; i.e., the business actors, application components, nodes, etc., that realize this behavior, and external active structure elements; i.e., the interfaces that expose this behavior to the environment.
    BehaviorElement
    BehaviorElement vnull Similar to active structure elements, behavior elements can be subdivided into internal behavior elements and external behavior elements; i.e., the services that are exposed to the environment.
    Event
    Event vnull An event may have a time attribute that indicates the moment or moments at which the event happens.
    ExternalActiveStructureElement
    ExternalActiveStructureElement vnull An interface provides an external view on the service provider and hides its internal structure.
    ExternalBehaviorElement
    ExternalBehaviorElement vnull
    InternalActiveStructureElement
    InternalActiveStructureElement vnull Internal active structure are the elements that realize the behavior exposed by external active structures.
    InternalBehaviorElement
    InternalBehaviorElement vnull
    PassiveStructureElement
    PassiveStructureElement vnull A passive structure element is a structural element that cannot perform behavior.
    StructureElement
    StructureElement vnull Structure elements are the strategic element resource, and structural elements, which can be subdivided into active structure elements and passive structure elements.
